2026-04-16 12:11:24 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 6'] hypothesis_explanation='All modules 1–5 pass 12 V correctly and have 0 V on their negative lines. At control module 6, measurements show the + input at ~12 V but the + output at 0 V, while downstream modules 7 and 8 see 0 V on all lines, so the supply is being interrupted or shorted within module 6. Visual/voltage tests also show the 12 V input lead to the module’s switch circuit is disconnected and floating, and the module’s indicator LED and series resistor are missing. This indicates that control module 6’s internal series path is faulty (open or miswired) so that its output is tied to 0 V instead of being switched from the 12 V input. Replacing or repairing control module 6 (including restoring the correct internal wiring and components) should restore 12 V continuity to modules 7–8 and the load, allowing their indicators and the lamp to operate when all switches are ON.'
